Sentencas: Lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) is an appreciable cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), and it has been widely investigated, owing to its excellent thermal and chemical stability.
Titulo: Enhanced cathodic activity by tantalum inclusion at B-site of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.6O3 based on structural property tailored via camphor-assisted solid-state reaction

Sentencas: However, its poor oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity, particularly at a temperature of <= 800 degrees C, causes setbacks in achieving a peak power density of > 1.0 W.cm(-2), limiting its application in the commercialization of SOFCs.
Titulo: Enhanced cathodic activity by tantalum inclusion at B-site of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.6O3 based on structural property tailored via camphor-assisted solid-state reaction

Sentencas: To improve the ORR of LSCF, doping strategies have been found useful.
Titulo: Enhanced cathodic activity by tantalum inclusion at B-site of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.6O3 based on structural property tailored via camphor-assisted solid-state reaction

Sentencas: Herein, the porous tantalum-doped LSCF materials (La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.57Ta0.03O3 (LSCFT-0), La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.57Ta0.06O3, and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.5Ta0.1O3) are prepared via camphor-assisted solid-state reaction (CSSR).
Titulo: Enhanced cathodic activity by tantalum inclusion at B-site of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.6O3 based on structural property tailored via camphor-assisted solid-state reaction

Sentencas: The LSCFT-0 material exhibits promising ORR with area-specific resistance (ASR) of 1.260, 0.580, 0.260, 0.100, and 0.06 Omega.cm(2) at 600, 650, 700, 750, and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Enhanced cathodic activity by tantalum inclusion at B-site of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.6O3 based on structural property tailored via camphor-assisted solid-state reaction

Sentencas: The performance is about 2 times higher than that of undoped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.6O3 with the ASR of 2.515, 1.191, 0.596, 0.320, and 0.181 Omega.cm(2) from the lowest to the highest temperature.
Titulo: Enhanced cathodic activity by tantalum inclusion at B-site of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.6O3 based on structural property tailored via camphor-assisted solid-state reaction

Sentencas: Through material characterization, it was found that the incorporated Ta occupied the B-site of the material, leading to the enhancement of the ORR activity.
Titulo: Enhanced cathodic activity by tantalum inclusion at B-site of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.6O3 based on structural property tailored via camphor-assisted solid-state reaction

Sentencas: With the use of LSCFT-0 as the cathode material for anode-supported single-cell, the power density of > 1.0 W.cm(-2) was obtained at a temperature < 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Enhanced cathodic activity by tantalum inclusion at B-site of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.6O3 based on structural property tailored via camphor-assisted solid-state reaction

Sentencas: The results indicate that the CS SR-derived LSCFT is a promising cathode material for SOFCs.
Titulo: Enhanced cathodic activity by tantalum inclusion at B-site of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.4Fe0.6O3 based on structural property tailored via camphor-assisted solid-state reaction
